msItem.note:
 Weekly canticles, most with titles: 

(1) Confitebor tibi domine (Isaiah 12) (‘Canticum ysaye
                                 prophete’);

(2) Ego dixi (Isaiah 38: 10–21) (‘canticum’);

(3) Exultauit cor meum (1 Samuel 2: 1–11) (‘Cantica
                                 anne’);

(4) Cantemus domino (Exodus 15: 1–20) (‘canticum moysi’);

(5) Domine audiui (Habakkuk 3) (‘Canticum abacuch
                                 prophete’);

(6) Audite celi (Deuteronomy 32: 1–44).

 Daily canticles, prayers and creeds, most with titles: 

(1) Te deum laudamus (‘hymnus augustini et ambrosij’) (fol.
                                 238r);

(2) Benedicite omnia opera (‘canticum trium puerorum’) (fol.
                                 239v);

(3) Benedictus dominus deus (‘canticum’) (fol. 241r);

(4) Magnificat (‘Canticum beate marie uirginis’) (fol.
                                 242r);

(5) Nunc dimittis (‘Canticum simeonis’) (fol. 242v);

(6) Gloria in excelsis (‘laus angelorum’) (fol. 243r);

(7) Apostles’ Creed (Credo in deum ... ) (fol. 243v);

(8) Nicene Creed (Credo in unum deum ... ) (‘Symbolum ecclesie’)
                                 (fol. 244r);

(9) Athanasian Creed (Quicumque uult ... ) (‘fides atanasi
                                 episcopi’) (fol. 245r).
                            Fols. 248v–253r are ruled but blank.
